Discussion. The taxonomic study of Chinese turbellarians started relatively late. At the end of the 20 th century, only 21 species of freshwater turbellarians were recorded (
Zhao et al. 2011
). Since the 21 st century, 30 more species of turbellarians have been described, including 18 species of Rhabdocoela (Wang 2004 ;
Wang & Li 2005
;
Wang & Wu 2005 a
,
2005 b
;
